==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mosasaurus
<hw>Mos`a*sau"rus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L.
<ets>Mosa</ets> the River Meuse (on which Meastricht is situated) + Gr.
<?/ a lizard.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>A genus of extinct marine
reptiles allied to the lizards, but having the body much elongated, and
the limbs in the form of paddles. The first known species, nearly fifty
feet in length, was discovered in Cretaceous beds near
<city>Maestricht</city>, in the Netherlands.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>Mososaurus</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moschatel</ent>⟦br⟧
